 $cc$ and final state $q_1q_2$ ($q_1$ and the original\n$q_2$ in initial state may be the same flavor quarks) which possess definite\nspin are no longer spectators. A rearrangement of quarks for initial and final\nstates is adopted to isolate the unchanged subsystem $cq_2$ which can be viewed\nas the spectator approximately. Future measurements on these channels will\nconstrain the nonperturbative parameter in the wavefunctions and test the model\npredictions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Mar 2023 07:32:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 12 Mar 2023 15:11:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-18"}
